Scenario 
I Type in a website (example: google.com) into my browser and press enter. Here is a step by step analysis on what happens and steps happen through the OSI model:

---

7. Application Layer
This is where the user interacts with the network
Browser sends request to access the website

What is Happening:
Browser prepares an HTTPS/HTTP request to send to sever
Browser can also use DNS to translate the website (google.com) into an IP address

My Understanding: 
This is the layer where the application talks to the network

---

6. Presentation Layer 
This layer acts as a translator for data to and from the application layer (layer 7) 

What is happening:
Data is formatted so that both sides understand it 
Data is encrypted at this layer using HTTPS 

My Understanding:
This layer acts as a translator for data and as an encryptor

---

5. Session Layer
This layer creates and maintains a stable connection between computer and server 

What is Happening: 
Establishes a secure connection between my computer and the web server im trying to request/recieve data from
When data is being sent from computer to server or vice versa, makes sure it establishes a secure connection

My understanding:
This layer keeps the connection between the webserver and computer stable

---

4. Transport Layer (IMPORTANT)
Decides what protocol to use when sending and receiving data either using TCP or UDP

What is Happening: 
TCP is used when you need to send and receive data accurately, TCP is slower, but more reliable.
TCP is commonly used for emails, texts, etc.
UDP is used for faster data recieves/requests, and is primarily used in gaming, live video streaming, etc. But doesn't check if the data you're requesting/receiving is accurate.

My understanding:
This layer makes sure whether data gets sent accurately, but slowly (TCP), or fast but not reliable (UDP)




